<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,740,1160]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,740,765]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Description.</emphasis>
Fragment of a narrow spire, H 
<number box="[649,700,740,764]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="14.8">14.8</number>
, D 9.0 mm. Protoconch eroded, probably paucispiral. Teleoconch of four whorls, the last broken. Whorls high, weakly convex, delineated by a deep, linear suture. Axial sculpture of strong but narrowly rounded costae, almost corresponding from whorl to whorl. No spiral sculpture. Costae opisthocline, rather straight. Columella with at least three folds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
